ll create extra work for you too since you will probably be reviewing that code as well.\n\nYes, but it will be less work than having to constantly point out bad commits.  In terms of my personal tradeoff, I\u0027d rather possibly have to revisit one script review than definitely have to revisit hundreds of reviews that get this stuff wrong on first patchset.  The goal is ultimately to make things get upstream easier, and I believe that on-balance, this patchset accomplishes that.\n\nIf you truly believe that this will make things harder to maintain, I\u0027m happy to hear it, but from my perspective, it makes things easier.",
