      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I would prefer we integrate these checks with the existing logic.\n\nIs that something you\u0027d like to put up a patch for?  I\u0027m not against it, I just don\u0027t understand why we\u0027re worried in this context and it doesn\u0027t rise to the level of necessary for me.  As written, this script runs in 160ms for all configs on my machine.  For comparison, even with parallel execution, the schema check takes 2.0 seconds on the same machine, and 54 seconds user.  That difference is why the other one requires a pool and this one doesn\u0027t.\n\n\nas an aside, I would be really curious to know why we even need a pool on validate_configs, and why it\u0027s so slow.  I\u0027d bet we\u0027re scanning in the schemas for every iteration, and wouldn\u0027t need the pool there if we just read them in at the start, but that\u0027s a guess.",
